A group of U.S. investors opposed toRoyal Dutch Shell Petroleum Co's South African policies plansto seek a special shareholders meeting to discuss theircomplaints.    Representatives of the American Baptist Churches and theNew York City Teachers Retirement System said the company hasrefused to include their proposals in proxy material preparedfor the annual meeting in May.    The group said its proposals call for an end to sales byRoyal Dutch to the South African police and military andwithdrawal from South Africa.   Reuter&#3;